cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces a new training framework for Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) to generate synthetic data. It also involves the use of differential privacy, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper specifically focuses on generating synthetic images, which is a common task in the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the use of GANs and differential privacy also falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), respectively.
